{
  "texts": [
    "When analyzing the mistakes of GPT-4, we found that most errors corresponded to lower-order cognitive levels, particularly \"remember\" and \"understand.\"",
    "While we found some mistakes for \"apply,\" very few or no errors were found for \"analyze\" and \"evaluate\" (\"create\" could not be assessed in this study).",
    "To the best of our knowledge, this study is the first to describe the cognitive levels at which GPT-4 makes mistakes in the context of psychosomatic medicine.",
    "This study has important implications.",
    "First, GPT-4 is already capable of answering many questions in (psychosomatic) medicine, and thus, should the technology be made available, it could reduce the effectiveness of summative assessment."
  ]
}